HEADWORD: Imbankment
<hw>Im*bank"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
surrounding with a bank; a bank or mound raised for defense, a roadway,
etc.; an embankment. See <er>Embankment</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imbannered</ent>⟦br⟧
